    "The model Fig. 9 The conversion from a geometry image to a point cloud is relatively easy, the inverse transformation is more difficult trains the images and their 3D point clouds simultaneously, achieving one-to-one mapping while learning a multimodal feature representation (Guo et al. 2019).",
    "By learning the shape of parts, this method achieves consistent 3D reconstruction.",
    "Similarly to the work of Wang and Yoon (2021), the main branch consists of a VAE, while an auxiliary branch is introduced for separate image encoding.",
    "Net is tested with synthetic images, while real-life evaluation is preserved for future work.",
    "Further optimizations are planned by experimenting with different losses and data structures."
